
[1]inflexibleness

   INFLEX'IBLENESS, n. [L. in and flexibilis, from flecto, to bend.]

   1. The quality of being inflexible, or not capable of being bent;
   unyielding stiffness.

   2. Obstinacy of will or temper; firmness of purpose that will not yield
   to importunity or persuasion; unbending pertinacity.
